  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Oil Wealth and Development in Uganda and Beyond,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2019, highlights the complex relationship between oil wealth and socioeconomic development in Uganda. While it currently holds a modest citation record in academic circles, it demonstrates significant potential for scholarly uptake and relevance in policy discussions on sustainability.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Oil Wealth and Development in Uganda and Beyond\" critically examines the implications of Uganda's burgeoning oil sector for development outcomes. Despite not yet accumulating citations, the book provides a foundational study that could catalyze discussions within both academic and policy-making communities, particularly given its topic's pressing relevance to sustainable development goals.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred strength of the book in terms of commercial linkage is notably high, with assessments indicating robust visibility on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. This presence suggests that the work may appeal not only to scholars but also to a broader audience interested in the intersections of natural resource management and economic development.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In terms of scholarly uptake, the book is poised to influence future research, with an inferred strength rating of 0.45. This suggests that as discussions around oil and development evolve, \"Oil Wealth and Development in Uganda and Beyond\" may become increasingly cited in subsequent work, particularly as Uganda\u2019s oil sector continues to develop.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book also aligns with sustainability and policy relevance, highlighted by its association with sustainable development goals. This alignment suggests its potential utility in informing policy frameworks aimed at maximizing the benefits of oil revenues in Uganda while minimizing environmental and social impacts, thus contributing to ongoing conversations on sustainable resource management.</p>",
